Sales Pipeline Database Structure.
Each column must be treated as follow:
1. Client Name - the name of the client - Input string 
2. Customer code - auto load from Client database
3. Product line - the service client bought from us - dropdown (Stracomm, SMM, Creative Strategy, Media Buying, Ads Manamgement, Production, Others)
4. Project Description - Description of the project
5. Project Type - Type of the project - dropdown (One-time or Retainer)
6. Sales - Sales Rep for the Account - Dropdown users with role account/ busdev
7. Stage - Stage of the project - dropdown (Leads, Pipeline, Negotiation, Closed Won, Lost Deal, Invoiced, Contract Renewal)
8. Projected Revenue - the projected revenue of the project - Number in Indonesian Rupiah
9. Billing Plan - the expected close month of the project - Input string (YY-MM)
10. Quarter - the expected quarter of the project - Calculated based on the billing plan (Q1 2026, Q2 2026, Q3 2026, Q4 2026)
11. Quotation Document - The proof of Quotation Document - Upload File PDF
12. Signed Quotation - The proof of Signed Quotation - Upload File PDF
13. Actual Revenue - the actual revenue of the project - Number in Indonesian Rupiah
14. Loss Deal Reason - if project stage is Lost Deal - String
15. Request Invoice - Send notification to Finance through email to do Invoicing - Button in UI (only if stage is Closed Won and once it is clicked, it will change to Invoiced)
16. Notes - additional notes about the client
